Rare is the opportunity to be able to work with such extraordinary women on a film. I feel extremely proud to create something so special with you all. ❤️

WAR PONY, a very special film I was lucky enough to work on will be out in theaters for one week only, starting Friday in the US. Please share and show support by watching this film in theaters. It’s so important to share indigenous stories and to be able to watch on the big screen. Love you all ❤️

A few more days to see War Pony in theaters. If you haven’t gone yet I urge you to see! Sharing some fitting photos from the film. The process of fittings for this one was unique in that we went all over the rez as everyone was so spread out. Love being able to spend time with each person in their homes, made the process much more intimate. Thank you to everyone for welcoming me and sharing your stories. I’ll love this film forever for that.
Might just be one of my favorite places of all time, magic ✨🇹🇷

I’ve gone through various phases in my personal style over the years but one thing that’s always stayed consistent is the way I’ve incorporated sportswear into my everyday style. (I will forever be a hoodie girly from the bay, swipe for context.) I played all the sports growing up, and that style has been something thats stayed with me all these years. Wearing Nike was always the goal and I feel so blessed to be part of the #nikewomen #teamnike

Women dressing women is an exhibition at the Met I loved for a few reasons. One of which explores the idea that though we haven’t always been credited for our work, we’ve been behind the scenes historically for hundreds of years. The impact that we carry is tremendous and it’s a nice reminder that what we do is important. Love these photos of work rooms over the years so thought I’d share.
